text.section:
In determining the amount of any financial penalty or forfeiture to be imposed under this section, the Commissioner:
shall consider the following factors:
the seriousness of the violation;
the good faith of the violator;
the violator's history of previous violations;
the deleterious effect of the violation on the public and the insurance industry; and
the assets of the violator; and
may determine the appropriate amount of the penalty or forfeiture.
